The officer concerned shall take care to join at the place of posting within the prescribed period as per the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption of office, non-serving service and Provisions during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981 or else, if he fails to join the office of this post, his absence shall be deemed to be a "non-working day" (885). If received, they must be returned to the relevant authorities by post, registered at the original address.

7. The concerned shall note that in case of non-acceptance of appointment immediately under the said order or attempt to cancel the transfer under any kind of pressure, disciplinary action shall be taken against them on the ground that the act violates Rule 23 of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Conduct of Business) Rules, 1979, treating it as misconduct.
